In Lean 4, we can use the fact that the harmonic series diverges logarithmically. Specifically, we have the inequality `Real.log (n + 1) ≤ ∑ k ∈ Icc 1 n, (k : ℝ)⁻¹`. This can be shown by induction on `n`.

