  -- then π x is also unbounded above.
  -- Let's choose x = e^(N+1). Then log x = e^(N+1). We need π x > N.
  -- From (1), log x ≤ π x + 1. So π x ≥ log x - 1 = e^(N+1) - 1.
  -- For large N, e^(N+1) - 1 is much larger than N. So this works.
